{{unsourced|date=August 2016}}
[[Taiwan]] has been controlled by various governments and has been associated with various flags throughout its history. Since 1945, the [[Taiwan|Republic of China]] controls the island; thus the flag most commonly associated with it is the [[Flag of the Republic of China]].
{{Commons category|Flags of the Republic of China}}
==National flags== {| border="2" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" style="margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse;" |- bgcolor="#efefef" ! width="110"|Flag!!width="100"|Duration!!width="250"|Use!!width="250"|Description |- |[[file:Flag of the Republic of China.svg|border|100px]] ||1945- |Flag of the [[Republic of China]]. |A red field, with a blue canton containing a 12-ray white sun. |}
