This is a list of [[town]]s and [[village]]s in [[Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha]], consisting of the island of [[Saint Helena]], [[Ascension Island]] and the islands of [[Tristan da Cunha]].
==[[Ascension Island]]==
{| class="wikitable" border="1" |- ! Settlement ! Other name(s) ! Notes |- | [[Georgetown, Ascension Island|Georgetown]] | | The main civilian settlement on Ascension and its [[capital city|capital]]. |- | [[Two Boats, Ascension Island|Two Boats Village]] | Two Boats | A civilian village, with [[Two Boats School|the island's school]]. |- | [[Cat Hill, Ascension Island|Cat Hill]] | Main Base | The United States' main military base on the island. |- | [[Traveller's Hill]] | | [[Royal Air Force]] camp. |}
<small>[[RAF Ascension Island|Wideawake Airfield]] (RAF ''Ascension Island'') is a fifth area of settlement, but is not a centre of population.</small>
==[[Saint Helena|Saint Helena Island]]== [[Image:St-Helena-Jamestown-from-above.jpg|280px|right|thumb|View of [[Jamestown, Saint Helena|Jamestown]].]] {| class="wikitable" border="1" |- ! Settlement ! Other Name(s) ! Notes |- | [[Jamestown, Saint Helena|Jamestown]] | City of James Town<ref name="city">[http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2009/1751/schedule/made The St Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha Constitution Order 2009] "...and declared Jamestown to be a city called the “City of James Town”" (Schedule Preamble)</ref> | Jamestown is the capital of Saint Helena and the territory of Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha. It is also formally a city.<ref name="city"/> |- | Haytown | | Small settlement located in Jamestown district, in Rupert's Valley. |- | [[Half Tree Hollow]] | | Half Tree Hollow is now the most populous settlement in Saint Helena; began as a suburb of Jamestown. |- | [[Ladder Hill]] | | An older settlement in Half Tree Hollow district, at the top of Jacob's ladder. |- | [[Saint Paul's, Saint Helena|Saint Paul's]] | | Location of the Governor's residence and the Anglican cathedral. |- | [[Alarm Forest|Briars Village]] | | Part of the Alarm Forest district; effectively a suburb of Jamestown. |- | [[Barren Ground, Saint Helena|Barren Ground]] | | Part of the Blue Hill district. |- | Broadbottom | Broad Bottom | Part of the Blue Hill district. |- | [[Blue Hill, Saint Helena|Blue Hill Village]] | Blue Hill | |- | [[Levelwood, Saint Helena|Levelwood]] | | |- | [[Longwood, Saint Helena|Longwood]] | | |- | Hutt's Gate | | In Longwood district. |- | Bamboo Hedge | | Main settlement of [[Sandy Bay, Saint Helena|Sandy Bay]] district. |- | New Ground | | In St Paul's district. |- | Thompson's Hill | | In St Paul's district. |- |}
==[[Tristan da Cunha]]== [[Image:Tristan da Cunha4.jpg|280px|right|thumb|[[Edinburgh of the Seven Seas]]]]
{| class="wikitable" border="1" |- ! Settlement ! Other Name(s) ! Notes |- | [[Edinburgh of the Seven Seas]] | Edinburgh, Settlement of Edinburgh, The Settlement | Edinburgh of the Seven Seas is the capital of Tristan da Cunha, and is the only [[Human settlement|settlement]] in the archipelago† |}
