{{Orphan|date=October 2013}}

'''Magarat''' is Geographical cluster of Federal Republic of Nepal which existed in the History of Nepal from Budhigandki River in the East to [[Ghaghara River|Karnali River]] in the West.<ref name=Magarat>{{cite web|last=Rana|first=B.K.|title=KING ARAMUDI AND OTHER MAGAR RULERS OF NEPAL|url=https://sites.google.com/site/rana1616/king-aramudi-and-other-magar-rulers-of-nepal|accessdate=8 January 2013}}</ref>  It included 12& 18 small kingdoms (excluding [[Palpa District|Palpa]] and Gorkha which are considered to be among the strongest kingdom of Nepal) of that time scattered in the modern territory of Nepal before the [[Unification of Nepal]] by [[Prithivi Narayan Shah]]. Magarat is considered to be the place settled and inhabited by Magars, the largest Indigenous Ethnic Groups of Nepal.
[[File:Kauda dance.jpg|thumb|Magar girls clad in traditional attire perform Kauda,the traditionaln Magar dance.]]

