{{redirect|Silverband|the type of musical group|silver band}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2014}} {{Use Australian English|date=September 2014}} {{Infobox waterfall | name = Silverband Falls | photo = 20090614 Silverband Falls - Grampians National Park - Victoria - Australia.JPG | photo_width = 270px | photo_caption = The Silverband Falls, located in the [[Grampians National Park]] | map = Australia Victoria | map_width = 270 | map_caption = Location of the Silverband Falls in [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]] | relief = yes | coords = {{coord|37|9|10|S|142|31|40|E|region:AU-VIC_type:waterbody_source:kolossus-eswiki|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <ref>{{Cite VICNAMES|122634|Silverband Falls|accessdate=17 November 2014}}</ref> | location = [[Grampians (region)|Grampians]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], [[Australia]] | type = Horsetail | elevation = | height = | height_longest = | number_drops = 1 | width = | average_width = | watercourse = Dairy Creek | average_flow = | world_rank = }} The '''Silverband Falls''' are [[waterfalls]] located in the [[Grampians National Park]], in western [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], [[Australia]]. Fed by Dairy Creek, the horsetail falls are characterised by a narrow band of water that tumbles over a small rock face and then disappears into a rocky base. The creek re-emerges some {{convert|50|m}} west of the falls.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.world-of-waterfalls.com/australia-silverband-falls.html|title=Silverband Falls|work=World of Waterfalls|author=Cheng, Johnny T.|date=|accessdate=17 November 2014}}</ref>
Early European visitors to the falls named it Silverband because of its narrow stream of water.
