{{Infobox book | name = Tears We Cannot Stop: A Sermon to White America | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | author = [[Michael Eric Dyson]] | audio_read_by = | title_orig = | orig_lang_code = | title_working = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | series = | release_number = | subject = | set_in = | publisher = [[St. Martin's Press]]<ref name=KR/> | publisher2 = | pub_date = | english_pub_date = | published = January 17, 2017 | media_type = Print, [[e-book]] | pages = 240 pp<ref name=KR/> | awards = | isbn = 978-1-250-13599-5 | isbn_note = | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | native_wikisource = | wikisource = | notes = | exclude_cover = | website = }}
'''''Tears We Cannot Stop: A Sermon to White America''''' is a 2017 non-fiction book by [[Michael Eric Dyson]].<ref name=KR>[https://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-reviews/michael-eric-dyson/tears-we-cannot-stop/ Kirkus Reviews]</ref><ref>[http://mobile.nytimes.com/2017/01/04/magazine/michael-eric-dyson-believes-in-individual-reparations.html The New York Times]</ref>
==Overview== A look into the current states of [[race and ethnicity in the United States|race relations in the United States]]. Written through the bias opinion of Michael Eric Dyson, explaining how even in 2018, there is a clear divider between whites and blacks.
