The '''Timeline of Earth science satellites''' shows, in chronological order, those successful [[satellite]]s with a program of [[Earth science]]. [[Sputnik 1]], while the first satellite ever launched, did not conduct Earth science. [[Explorer 1]] was the first satellite to make an Earth science discovery when it found the [[Van Allen belts]]. {{Expand list|date=August 2008}}
